# Built binaries
/satelle
/cmd/satelle/satelle

# Legacy pre-rebrand state. The old `satellites` CLI (V5) writes a workspace
# state dir at ./.satellites/ in whatever cwd it runs in. satelle (V6) uses
# .satelle/ exclusively; .satellites/ is dead and must never be tracked. Ignore
# the whole dir so a stray legacy invocation can't be staged or committed.
# See docs/legacy-satellites-dir.md.
/.satellites

# satelle's own .satelle/ local state is governed by the managed block below
# (added by `satelle init`): the local database is ignored, while the committed
# satelle.toml and the authored markdown under .satelle/ stay tracked — satelle
# dogfoods itself.

# >>> satelle (managed) >>>
# satelle's per-repo database is local state — ignore it and its sidecars, plus
# the per-user config overlay. The committed satelle.toml and the authored
# markdown under .satelle/ stay tracked.
.satelle/satelle.db
.satelle/satelle.db-wal
.satelle/satelle.db-shm
.satelle/satelle.local.toml
# the repo-local pinned binary (satelle update --local) is local state, never committed
.satelle/satelle
# the per-story markdown mirror is regenerated from the local database (the
# source of truth); the files are portable but not versioned in this repo.
.satelle/stories/
# task work-definition files are authored substrate (the file is the source of
# truth, the DB its index — sty_c1f9e74c) but, like the local database and story
# state, they are per-repo LOCAL work, not versioned here.
.satelle/tasks/
# the flat operation log (a read-only reviewer's read surface) is local evidence
.satelle/logs/
# <<< satelle (managed) <<<

# commit-push gate artifacts — the PR-style commit summaries the commit-push
# reviewer writes are generated and read locally per story; they are review
# artifacts, not version-controlled.
.satelle/documents/commit-summary-*.md
# OKF bundle-root index / changelog — regenerated locally from the documents
# (which here are the ignored commit summaries), so they are local artifacts too.
.satelle/documents/index.md
.satelle/documents/log.md
